issue.body:
Clang at -Os produces the wrong code.

Bisected to 19918ac34dc5d304ec6ad413ceae1d4394abe28f, which was committed by @fhahn 

Compiler explorer: 

```console
% cat reduced.c
int printf(const char *, ...);
int a, c = 1, e;
long b;
static int *d = &a;
int main() {
  int *f = &c;
  for (; b <= 6; b++)
    *d ^= *f;
  int **g = &d;
  int **h = &d;
  b = &g == &h;
  printf("%d\n", a);
}
% clang -O0 a.c && ./a.out
1
% clang -Os a.c && ./a.out
0
%
```
